OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise by more than
OL,4,Cexpected as Ofgem increases price cap
OL,6,FEnergy prices will rise by 6.4% in
OL,7,FApril under energy watchdog Ofgem's
OL,8,Fnew price cap, representing a higher-
OL,9,Fthan-expected rise in energy bills.
OL,11,FOfgem said the rise will equate to
OL,12,F#111 for an average household per
OL,13,Fyear, or around #9.25 a month, over
OL,14,Fthe three-month period of the price
OL,15,Fcap.
OL,17,FThe increase means the total average
OL,18,Fbill will rise from #1,738 to #1,849
OL,19,Ffrom April 1 for a typical household
OL,20,Fin England, Scotland and Wales.
