OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise by more than
OL,4,Cexpected as Ofgem increases price cap
OL,6,FExperts had forecast bills to rise by
OL,7,Fabout 5%, because of an increase in
OL,8,Fgas prices across Europe, caused by a
OL,9,Fslump in the amount of gas held in
OL,10,Fstorage across the continent.
OL,12,FThe energy price cap sets a maximum
OL,13,Fprice that energy companies can charge
OL,14,Fpeople in England, Scotland and Wales
OL,15,Ffor each unit of energy they use.
OL,17,FOfgem changes the price cap for
OL,18,Fhouseholds every three months. The new
OL,19,Fprice cap will run from April 1 until
OL,20,FJuly.
